latestIgtvVideos.title: DATE NIGHT HAIR TUTORIAL 🌹
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
A quick + easy date night look using @FEKKAI‘s ‘full blown volume’ collection. Start by washing hair with Full Blow Volume Shampoo & Conditioner…
1.) create a deep side part and clip back the smaller section of hair 
2.) spray roots and length with texturizing spray and brush through
3.) using a wide barrel curling wand (I’m using the @T3micro 1.5” barrel), section hair and curl away from your face. This will create a soft wave. Repeat on the smaller section of hair 
4.) place clips in a half circle around your ear, securing the section 
5.) finish the look with texturizing spray

latestPosts.caption:
just when you thought a Hugo spritz couldn’t get any better 😋 this was dangerously good, here’s how to make it:

Ingredients
- 1 1/2 cups @proseccodoc_usa 
- 1/2 cup @stgermaindrinks 
- 1/4 fresh lime juice 
- 2-3oz mint simple syrup (easy recipe below)

1. Combine all ingredients into your @ninjakitchen Creami container and freeze overnight
2. Spin once on the ‘sorbet’ setting and serve 

**mint simple syrup - bring 1/4 cup of water to a boil, add 3-4 mint tea bags and steep for 5 mins. remove teabags and add 1/4 cup of white sugar. stir sugar until dissolved in hot water and allow to cool before using in recipe**

summertime ready ☀️ save this for your long weekend plans! 

frozen paloma recipe (makes one cocktail): 
- 1 large ruby red grapefruit
- 1 lime juiced 
- 2 oz @donjuliotequila blanco tequila 
- 1/2 can of lemon lime @drinkpoppi 

1. cut grapefruit in half, juice half and break second half into smaller chunks. add chunks and juice to an ice cube tray and freeze overnight 

2. add frozen grapefruit, lime juice, tequila & poppi to a blender (adding more ice as needed) 

3. garnish glass with tajin & serve

salmon bowls are back on the menu! I overdid it and had to take a little break (😅), but hot honey salmon is back on rotation 

recipe:
- 2-3 salmon fillets, cut into small chunks
- 1/2 cup honey
- 3 tbsp. hot sauce
- Cayenne pepper
- Paprika
- Chipotle chili powder
- Garlic powder
- Onion powder
- Rice 
- 1 avocado
- 1 jalapeno, seeded & chopped
- Dill
- Sesame seeds
- Edamame (love the pre shelled pack from Trader Joes)

1. Toss salmon in EVOO and paprika, bake at 450F for 10-15 mins.

2. Make hot honey sauce using honey, hot sauce, cayenne, paprika, chipotle chili powder, garlic, and onion powder (all to taste). Pour half of sauce over salmon and broil for 2-4 minutes. 

3. Combine avocado, jalapeño, EVOO, dill, & sesame seeds. 

4. (Optional) mix nonfat plain greek yogurt, chopped chives, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, & onion powder for a creamy “ranch”. 

5. Assemble bowl with cooked rice, salmon, avocado salsa, & edamame. Spoon additional hot honey sauce over top of salmon, top with a dollop of creamy ranch, & sprinkle with sesame seeds. 

#weeknightdinner #easymeals #salmonbowl #dinnerforone #dinnerprep #easyrecipeideas

sophie’s summer waves 🌊 my hair is a bit curlier than the mamma mia character so I tried to minimize definition & volume for this softer wavy look ✨

+ style hair WET & brush style in large sections to keep curl clumps together 

+ leave your hair plopped in a microfiber towel for at least at hour to absorb water 

+ hover diffuse instead of scooping to minimize volume (even better if you can air dry)
